        <h2 id="potage">Potage le Magnifique</h2>
        <img src="https://www.undergearedovercooked.com/uploads/1/6/4/9/16494292/dsc-0213.jpg?1054">
        <ul>
            <li>Time: however long it takes</li>
            <li>Serves: one, I think</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th> 
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>chicken broth</td>
                    <td> 4 cups</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>beef broth</td>
                    <td> 4 cups</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>butter</td>
                    <td> 2 1/2 ounces</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>flour</td>
                    <td> 1 wooden flagon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>diced carrots</td>
                    <td> 1 cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>diced onions</td>
                    <td> 1/2 cup</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong>  Stoke the flames of your open-pit fire, and achieve a low heat.
</p>
    <p><strong>Step 2:</strong>  Combine all ingredients into a large soup pot.
</p>
    <p><strong>Step 3:</strong>  Stir vigorously!
</p>
   <p><strong>Step 4:</strong>  Once hot, pour into earthen soup bowls immediately!
</p>
    <p><em>Source: <a href="https://www.engadget.com/2011/11/23/joystiq-of-cooking-skyrims-potage-le-magnifique/">Joystiq of cooking</a></em></p>
    
